caption: Today I ordered from Oasis for the first time. I'm vegan and I've been hearing great things from this place! But today they had a pop-up, serving a seitan gyro. I ordered online, drove for 25 minutes to get there and when I arrived, they told me it would be a half hour more, because of all the orders they got. I can't describe the amazing treatment I got from the lady on the phone. She was so positive, understanding, calm and excellent at customer service! So much so, that I decided to wait in my car for that half an hour. When I got home with my vegan gyro, I could not believe how GOOOOOD it was! AND, they gave me a complimentary huge order of hummus, that's gonna last me a while in the fridge. Simply delicious, good service, even when they had a one hour delay! I can't say good enough things about this place. Please keep catering to us vegans!
I love this place. Nothing but great experiences here. Bring your hunger - portions are large.
One of the best place for wraps ... grilled vegetables OMG so tasty

Hummus, falafel, pita, and sauces are all great and the staff is very friendly. Excited to try the rest of the menu  If you want their hummus & pita but can't make it downtown, grab them at Hyvee...way better that all the other brands!

Love these guys! Support small local businesses! Everything I've had there is scrumptious! Many many vegan options! That baba ghanoush is dreamy! And they have the best wheat pita bread I've ever had!
One of the best spots of its kind in the area. This place has a cool feel to it. This place has great reviews for a reason.
Cool location to meet with coworkers. The service was very friendly and attentive. The bill was decent. I can see why they have so many great reviews.
It's so tasty. The service was very welcoming and observant. Bring your appetite because portions are large.
This place does it for me. Nothing but pleasant experiences here. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
menu is similar to a restaurant in jacksonville i loved.
looking forward to a return visit. the prices are good for what you get. food is similar to a cafe in indianapolis i loved.

Food was absolutely fabulous. The two people who were out on the street to help me were more than kind since I couldn't go inside the restaurant because of covid-19 restrictions. They advised me about my gluten-free choices and warned me where cross-contaminations might occur. They were just so kind and helpful. This is a difficult time for all of us, but places like this make it worth the trouble to try.. even though I live 60 plus miles away I will return to this wonderful place.
Excellent and Authentic! Order online or by phone for pick up or delivery over noon.
You won't be disappointed in the menu and service. I'll return family next time. The prices are fair for the quality of food.
The BEST Falafel and hummus in Omaha! It is my absolutely favorite lunch spot and has great vegetarian and vegan options.
Food was so yummy. Service is consistently good.
this location is one of my favorites. looking forward to coming back with my friends. it has a good feel to it. makes me feel like i am back in sacramento.
this place will surprise you. the staff was very helpful and welcoming.

I hate the taste of falafels okay, and there falafels were so delicious perfectly flavored and perfectly crispy for a nice crunch. I ordered the cauliflower loaded fries and they were absolutely spectacular! On top of that it was 100% vegan which is super hard to find in Omaha! On top of all of that it was so freaking amazing and easy to order online! Just look how delicious my lunch was, my only complaint is that they're only open for lunch!! I don't eat out for lunch often and I wish I had more opportunities to eat here.
So tasty! Really good falafel and hummus, everyone in our party really enjoyed the food.  100% will return!
I love Oasis.  I really do.  You should try it.  I promise you won't regret it.  Best hummus and falafel in town.
Perfect ice cream.
Amazing food, great people. Don’t forget to take home a hummus or two, it’s the some of the best you’ll ever taste.
Best hummus
Food is always amazingly fresh.
The hummus and pita are both homemade and ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ the falafel are amazing
Would not have found this place except for Find Me Gluten Free. Great food and knowledge staff. Tried many things and it was all very good!
The front lady was so rude!!! So rude!!!
GF items clearly marked, knowledgeable staff.
Best falafel.good food
I just love this place! Always such a great experience, delicious food and lovely staff! And I always have leftovers!
Good food. Friendly staff. Would definitely recommend.
Food is always amazing and the owners couldn't be nicer. Support this great local business by visiting the restaurant or purchasing their hummus in grocery stores!
Delicious
So awesome to eat one of my Iowa City favorites in Omaha!!!! Food is exactly like it is at the flagship. Now have my place to stock up on hummus.
The food was amazingly good, each plate had its own unique taste. I love the place and the staff was very friendly. Highly recommend it
Excellent lunch spot, great falafel, and the best hummus in Omaha. I recommend the babaganoush as well, very tasty.
This was a great find on our weekend trip to Omaha.  It was a short walk from our hotel, and the food was amazing.  I had the chicken shawarma and it was amazing

Excellent food across the board. Wonderful selections of colourful, flavorful, ethnic dishes that compliment each other. Had a lovely conversation with Michael the owner and I will definitely be there frequently.
The falafel has a very crispy outside and soft inside. Perfection! Different kinds of fries too. The flavor experience was magical 👍🏻👍🏻
I agree that having a 1/2 kebab plate as an option would be great!
Oasis is always on the hit. Chef Mike is the real deal!! Best falafel in town IMHO. Just had the Tunisian Meatball Pita and couldn’t stop eating it. Great food, great service every time.
Love the food!
Very friendly and helpful
Great customer service and awesome food!

I thought I had had Falafel before... but after Oasis, realized everywhere else I’ve had it in Omaha does not come close to how good it is here.  We originally went for my gluten allergy wife as I am a meat eater but ... I can get behind this falafel for sure.    I just said Falafel more times in this post than I think I have in my life.
Very good spicy falafel pita! They have wheat or white options on pita too.

Amazing! Everything tasted tangy and fresh. I felt like I wanted to try one of everything on the menu. Here's the rundown of what I did try:  Falafel: crispy on the outside, perfect on the inside. Definitely leaves Amsterdam in the dust. Hummus: a tiiiiiiiiny bit spicy. Not an issue for anyone with a normal palate, but a heads up if you're sensitive to that because I would not expect it in hummus. Babaghanoush: amazing. Smooth and less eggplanty than most I have had. Tzatziki: chunky, more of the consistency of spinach artichoke dip than the usual yogurty dip. Labneh: so good. Thick and tangy and yum Zaatar fries: tastes exactly as you'd expect. Doesn't have the weird dryness of Amsterdam curry fries, but also not as crispy. Pita: super soft and fluffy  Note that the dining room isn't anything special and you order at the counter.
The food is really good and they have a nice service. Lots of vegetarian,  vegan and gluten free options available
I've been to Oasis twice now and I must say, they have some of the best hummus I've ever had! I think their food tastes really fresh and I'll definitely be adding them to my lunch rotation.
Delicious food. Quaunt setting.
Hummus is made here locally and is delicious. Bring some home.
This place it’s one and only!
Delicious gyro, had two falafel in it :) Staff was super friendly and I would go back
Great food! Fast service! Plates are large though. Would come more often if there was 1/2 kebab plate option, one gyro and one side with pita would be perfect
Consistently delicious
Awesome!!!
Food well prepared and tasty. Clean and pleasant environment. Excellent friendly service. Great experience all around.

I try to avoid superlatives, but for this place I'll make an exception. Hands down the best falafel I have ever eaten. Two bites into my pita it became immediately apparent why every seat in the restaurant was occupied. Great food, exceptional staff, and excellent value.

I can not rave enough about this place. I make it a point to eat here once a month, if not more. The food is delicious and the staff is awesome. Two of the nicest people you'll EVER meet. If you're downtown, try it. You won't be disappointed !!!
delicious food and awesome staff. great place for vegans to eat
Good food. Not so great background music
Amazing!! Legit enough said. Service is always great and owners are very nice. If you are looking for a good cheap eat this is your place!
Hands down one of my favorite places to find amazing vegan food!!
Wow, amazing food. The tzatziki is by far the best I have found. Was slightly disappointed in the gyro meat, didn't seem to be on par with the rest of the items.
Everything was really tasty. The za'atar fries were a nice spin on the the traditional. A little on the pricier side, but portions were good. I'll be back for sure!
Nice food and options... Generous and quick service. I liked the mango sauce
Great food that they are happy to help with ordering
Good Mediterranean food, the prices are a bit high for what you get. Lots of variety and choices.

This is an outstanding restaurant.  The falafel is so delicious; fried fresh and served hot and crispy.  The hummus is the best I've ever had, the fried pitas are amazing and the service is personal and friendly.  So many options to choose from (and they'll help you decide if you aren't quite sure what to get). There is an obvious commitment to quality at Oasis!
Great Mediterranean food, falafel is on point! Get the sultan's platter you choose four items and get pita with it! Great!

I've eaten here 3 times and I plan to go back. I love the variety they have on the menu and that the menu has designations for items that are GF and vegan. I love that they allow you a long list of side items to choose from. My fave are the shawarma and veggie kebabs and the red cabbage salad. The service is fast, the prices are reasonable. I don't like the unisex bathrooms because there is always a small puddle of pee in front of the toilets.
Fresh, flavorful food.  Everyone was super friendly too.  I want to eat everything on the menu.  Za'atar fries were especially good.  We have a punch card now so definitely going back.

Holy Falafel Batman! This is some SERIOUSLY good Mediterranean eats.  I'm not particularly "into" falafel, but I am into good food, and thus spot ticks that box. I got the lamb pita special, and it truly blew me away. The goat cheese brought a nice creamyness to the pita, and the falafel itself was very flavorful. The mango sauce they have ...oh my wordddd it's to die for. Drizzle it on everything to take it up 3 notches.  At the time that I went, this place had about 50 5-star ratings. Not a single 4 star rating, and I could see why. The staff was super friendly and incredibly helpful, valuable help as well! Not just lame recommendations that don't give you much info.  The inside of the place is a little funky looking, but don't let that deter you from getting some really amazing food.  Stuff my life into that pita /10
The falafel pita is the best falafel pita/sandwich/wrap I've had in years. Hands down.
Delicious food and great service, even though it was a busy lunch rush. The restaurant is a great space and there was plenty of room to accommodate a stroller. Will definitely be eating here again!
Amazing falafel, highly recommend the Mediterranean salad and the labneh with your falafel. Will be back next time I’m in Omaha.
Solid Mediterranean food
I really like going here over lunch. The staff is extremely friendly, and they are a great place to get some things you can't find in most restaurants in Omaha
High quality ingredients, great recipes and liberal use of spices. Price is reasonable as well.

We’re so glad we found this place! Great extensive menu that allows you to personalize plates to your taste. Quality food, friendly service and attention from owner operators. We loved it and see why it has such good reviews. Try it!

Consistently fabulous restaurant with great people and workers. The restaurant is open and inviting,  the food is tasty and they are able and willing to accommodate for vegans and gluten free needs. I love this place!

So many vegan options, so little time! The best hummus and baba ganoush ANYWHERE, and you can buy it takeout from the deli case as well. One of my favorites is their pita falafel. The owners are fabulously welcoming. Loyalty punch-card and regular specials keep me coming back again and again.
Super good food and very nice people!

Best falafel in Omaha! I love that there are so many vegan options & they're clearly marked. The falafel pita with vegetable kebab is my go to, the veggies are always fresh & grilled perfectly! Fries are good too, & I love that they sell packs of pita & hummus.
Best falafel I’ve ever had and excellent service!
Not bad at all
I loved their lamb Kobab and their falafel was so very much .everything was wonderful.
Authentic, tasty, and reasonably priced.
Bring your appetite!  Recommend ordering ahead online to avoid the wait.

Just placed an order for pick-up last night. Everyone was thoroughly impressed. Very high quality food, especially considering the reasonble prices. Always appreciate restaurants that provide real vegan options (and not just one or two). Can't wait to order again and try more stuff!

Best gyro I have had in Omaha. Service time from order entered in system to food in hand and out the door 3 minutes. I even got samples. Staff is super friendly. Thought the baklava was overpriced but not sold elsewhere so what to do? Good eats.
Food is great and the crew are friendly. They alwats make you feel like family.
Amazing food and hospitality. Mike, the owner went out of his way to feel us welcomed.
I don't like falafel.. never have. I LOVED this place!!
The food is GREAT!! Small place, with personal service and yummy food. What more could one ask for?
By far the BEST place in Omaha for falafel, hummus, babaganosh, baklava, and pitas! Great prices and super friendly staff! They have an amazing selection of vegan items as well!!!

Finally! Comfort food through and through. I have been in love with Oasis in Iowa City. And seeing them in Omaha today- I couldn’t stop to taste that amazing falafel sandwich again. Believe me- You will not regret it!!!

Oasis gets a solid 5 from me. Absolutely delicious. Service was prompt and ahead of schedule. I got the sultan's plate with baba ghanoush, moroccan eggplant, zataar fries and falafel. Everything was perfect and in fact the BG and eggplant were among the best I have ever had. Definitely going to order from here again!
Great new place downtown for lunches, and they just opened for some dinner/evenings, too!  Best falafel I have had in the midwest.
All the Mediterranean classics in a bright, modern space with super friendly staff
Massive menu and great tasting food. Order a la carte or with a combo deal. My faves are the lamb kebob with spicy fries!

So good! I’ve heard great things about this place, and I got to finally try it. I wanted to try a little bit of everything, so I got Genie’s Plate, which is 3 sides, plus some pita bread. Everything I had was fresh and delicious. The pita was so soft and paired perfectly with the hummus that they provided. For dessert I got the baklava, which also was yummy. Highly recommend!
Excellent food. This place is quickly becoming a downtown Omaha favorite.  Ask for the spicy fries.
Great food.
Very good food and the portion sizes are generous!  Perfect for downtown lunch.

If you haven't tried Oasis falafel or are worried it's just a rehash of the restaurant which was in the location before: Go. Try. It.  You won't be just surprised, you'll be impressed.  They also have great take and go sort of picnic lunch options as well.
Yummy food, friendly service.
Tasty stuff -- great for vegans/vegetarians! Super friendly staff. 😀
Love it. Amazing place for lunch. Great food and great service!
Great selection.  Fair prices.  Veggies were fresh.  Gyro meat is pre-sliced.  Very green and eco-friendly.  Knowledgeable, Friendly and helpful staff.
Great flavors and variety from the Mediterranean.

Food was pretty good, however considering we live in America and when someone says sauce we mean something that can fill any kind and of space. I asked for the sauce of my gyro to not be there and I find that this sauce was at the bottom of the pita pocket. If it wasn't for that I'd have given this 4 stars. As for why not 5, I found the service lacking in character. I know food jobs suck, but at least pretend you like it. It was a little pricey too, but when in a city it's going to be pricey.
Best food in Omaha!

One of the best place to eat in Omaha. The falafels are really amazing and they have a good variety. The sides have a lot of options and the pita chips are best among the lot. I had the spiced lamb in pita pocket which was great. The hummus there is too good. The service is just the cherry on the top. They serve you with smile. A must go place and will recommend to anyone who asks me for a good place to eat.
Friendly people and great food.
Lots of options for making your own plate, or get one of their meals! Delicious food and even better service, the most friendly staff!

Fabulous experience going here. The food was wonderful and the employees were fantastic. Really helpful and willing to go any extra mile to make sure you meal is wonderful, you could even sample some items to make sure it’s right for you. Hummus was the best I’ve ever had, and a lovely falafel. Will certainly be back for more
Delicious kebab plate, definitely worth the price. Left full and happy with some leftover Turkish coffee.

Went there today for the first time. It was my first time there and they were super helpful and patient with me while deciding what I wanted. The food was delicious (OMG the falafel!), fresh, and cooked perfectly. The restaurant was spotlessly clean, and I look forward to going back!
Well prepared and tasty!

AMAZING AMAZING AMAZING!!! Everything was absolutely wonderful. They staff were fantastic and took lots of time to answer my many questions. Very comfortable seating and extremely clean. I love the decor especially in the bathroom. Such a joyful experience. One of the best parts for me was the children's area and having a family restroom with a diaper changing area. Lots of options including plenty of plant based, gluten free, food sensitive, keto, and other dietary restrictions so everyone is happy. The portion sizes are extremely generous. My only issue is they aren't open enough but I was told they would be adding more hours soon. Oh they even have window seating for some extra atmosphere. We will definitely be back.
11/10 Sabich was really good.
Very good Greek food, the bobaganoosh Is a must also the chicken Kafka is also really great, will go again!

The food is so delicious that my friends at work and I have a "Falafel Friday" every week. Their vegan options are not only vegans' but also meat eaters' favorites. I'm so glad to have this restaurant close to my work and home. I just wish they would open after 5pm and on weekends.

Clean facility, friendly staff, and excellent food. Had the falafel pita. Was probably the best I’ve ever had. Everything was fresh and well prepared. Falafel was crispy, just the right consistency inside, and flavorful. The pita and hummus were also excellent. Nice job Oasis, keep it up!
Will be back. Came here for lunch today and ordered more to take home with me. Great food!
If you like Falafel, this place hard to beat! Fresh!
Fantastic food! Have only been dissappointed by the fact that I can’t stay there and live off of their food! Highly recommend!

Wow, this new restaurant is amazing! I ate the falafel sandwich and babba ganoush, both delicious. The falafel was cooked wonderfully. They even season the veggies for the sandwich! Very friendly staff. A+, can't wait to go back and try more of their menu.  If you are on the fence, this place is absolutely worth a try.
All delicious food

I am OBSESSED! Everything we tried was absolutely delightful. The falafel is perfectly crunchy, the hummus is bomb. Pretty much everything is VEGAN, including their Tahini sauce! Say whaaat?! The Turkish coffee is such a treat, and they have these sweet pita chips, which is fried pita bread with cinnamon. Thanks for bringing this to Omaha!
